  "narrative_arc": "Gay stick-up artist who robs drug dealers with a code — he never targets civilians. Simon uses Omar to document the parallel legal system of the street — its own courts (respect), its own penalties (violence), its own honor code. Omar navigates the street system more skillfully than the police navigate the legal one.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Omar's dome maps the shadow legal system. Layer 1 (Legal) has two versions in his dome — the formal law that hunts him and the street law he enforces. Building his dome reveals how informal justice systems emerge when formal ones are absent or hostile.",
